02%2Fb14200%2Fstatements_6009.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3APL%2FSQL\" class=\"Z3988\"></span></span>\r\n</li>\r\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\r\n<link rel=\"mw-deduplicated-inline-style\" href=\"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1133582631\"/><cite id=\"CITEREFGupta2012\" class=\"citation book cs1\">Gupta, Saurabh K. (2012). \"5: Using Advanced Interface Methods\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=Hq1KDAAAQBAJ\"><i>Advanced Oracle PL/SQL Developer's Guide</i></a>. Professional experience distilled (2&#160;ed.). Birmingham: Packt Publishing Ltd (published 2016). p.&#160;143. <a href=\"/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ISBN (identifier)\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781785282522\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9781785282522\"><bdi>9781785282522</bdi></a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2017-06-08</span></span>. <q>Whenever the PL/SQL runtime engine encounters an external procedure call, the Oracle Database starts the extproc process. The database passes on the information received from the call specification to the <code>extproc</code> process, which helps it to locate the external procedure within the library and execute it using the supplied parameters. The <code>extproc</code> process loads the dynamic linked library, executes the external procedure, and returns the result back to the database.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=5%3A+Using+Advanced+Interface+Methods&amp;rft.btitle=Advanced+Oracle+PL%2FSQL+Developer%27s+Guide&amp;rft.place=Birmingham&amp;rft.series=Professional+experience+distilled&amp;rft.pages=143&amp;rft.edition=2&amp;rft.pub=Packt+Publishing+Ltd&amp;rft.date=2012&amp;rft.isbn=9781785282522&amp;rft.aulast=Gup